node.text:
Introducing the #SpiritofRollsRoyce, an anthology of stories from inspirational clients whose work, passions and lifestyle embody the marque’s ethos. In their own words, each defines what it means to experience a Rolls-Royce motor car. 

In this first episode, Jihan takes to the rocky terrains of Ras Al Khaimah to reflect on her relationship with the inimitable Phantom. 

For her, the model is the crown of Rolls-Royce’s dynamic range. Its luxurious architecture converges with her passion for design and personalisation, resulting in a #Bespoke work of art that speaks to Jihan's character and creative visions. 

Discover #RollsRoycePhantom; link in bio.

—

Introducing the #SpiritofRollsRoyce, an anthology of stories from inspirational clients whose work, passions and lifestyle embody the marque’s ethos. In their own words, each defines what it means to experience a Rolls-Royce motor car. 

In this first episode, Jihan takes to the rocky terrains of Ras Al Khaimah to reflect on her relationship with the inimitable Phantom. 

For her, the model is the crown of Rolls-Royce’s dynamic range. Its luxurious architecture converges with her passion for design and personalisation, resulting in a #Bespoke work of art that speaks to Jihan's character and creative visions. 

Discover #RollsRoycePhantom; link in bio.

—

The unmistakable silhouette of the Rolls-Royce Merlin engine, that famously powered the RAF’s Spitfire and Hurricane aircrafts to victory during WWII, is intricately embroidered into this #Bespoke Dawn’s Waterfall, featured between the rear seats.

The custom stitching is just one of a suite of Bespoke features in this car that is dedicated to the extraordinary courage of two Czech airmen who fought valiantly alongside RAF squadrons during the Second World War. 

Discover more; link in bio.

Masterfully threaded into the fine leather upholstery, the hand-finished Hawk and Stork crests represent the insignia of the two squadrons the airmen fought with during their service.
